<HEADLINE> Estrada Designated Philippines' Acting President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
said Monday that he will designate President-Elect and Vice
President Joseph Estrada as acting president next week for the
first time in six years.
</P>
<P>
Ramos will leave for Paris next week to receive personally the
1997 U.N. Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization peace
award.
</P>
<P>
Estrada, the main opposition candidate who won the May 11
presidential polls, will be the acting president during the
absence of Ramos.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine president and vice president are elected
separately.
</P>
<P>
In the past, when Ramos left for abroad, a committee headed by
the executive secretary used to run the day-to-day operation of
the government and it reported to the president daily or hourly as
the need arose using the latest telecommunications gadgets.
</P>
<P>
Estrada will take oath as the country's 13th president on June
30 when Ramos steps down after serving out a single six-year term.
</P>
</TEXT>
