<HEADLINE> 118 Filipino Fishermen Arrested in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian authorities have seized
12 Philippine-registered boats and arrested some 118 fishermen
caught illegally fishing within Indonesian waters, the Philippine
News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Reynaldo Martinez, officer in charge of the Department of
Foreign Affairs in the southern Philippines, was quoted as saying
he was informed by the Philippine Consulate in Manado, Indonesia,
of the incident.
</P>
<P>
According to the consulate, the 118 fishermen from General
Santos City in the southern Philippines were apprehended by
Indonesian naval authorities based in the southern Indonesian city
of Bitung.
</P>
<P>
But Martinez did not mention when the arrests were made.
</P>
<P>
The news agency said Filipino fishermen were often apprehended
by the Indonesian authorities for illegal entry or illegal
fishing.
</P>
<P>
Early this month, a group of six Filipino fishermen from
General Santos City were repatriated as part of a move to bring
back some 100 fishermen still languishing in Indonesian jails.
</P>
</TEXT>
