<HEADLINE> 5 Injured in Anti-BJP Demonstration in New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Five people including two
policemen were injured in stone pelting and cane charge during a
demonstration here on Monday by the Indian Youth Congress against
the alleged misrule by the government led by the Bharatiya Janata
Party (BJP).
</P>
<P>
Police said tear gas and water cannons were used to disperse
hundreds of demonstrators.
</P>
<P>
The Congress activists, in their attempt to march to the
parliament building, tried to break the barricade but were stopped
by water cannons. They later pelted stones at the cops who
retaliated by firing tear gas.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators shouted anti-BJP slogans and burned effigies
of BJP leaders including Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee and
Home Minister L. K. Advani.
</P>
<P>
They demanded the rollback of the retirement age to 58, which
the government decided in May to be extended to 60, restoration of
pre-budget oil prices and slashing of additional duties on
tractors and other items of mass consumption. 
</P>
</TEXT>
