<HEADLINE> 37 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A total of 37 Kurdish rebels have
been killed in the military operations staged by the Turkish
security forces in southeastern Turkey, an official statement
said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that the security forces had wiped out 23 PKK militants
in Kelmehmet mountainous areas in Sirnak province, 13 in Eruh
town of Siirt province and one in Kulp town of Diyarbakir
province.
</P>
<P>
One soldier of the security forces also died in the operations,
said the statement. However, the statement failed to disclose when
the PKK rebels were killed.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 14-year-old war for autonomy in
southeastern Turkey, which has claimed over 35,000 lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
