<HEADLINE> Britain Destroys 1,000 Landmines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The British Ministry of Defense
destroyed some 1,000 anti-personnel landmines in southern England
early Monday, implementing the country's landmine destruction
program.
</P>
<P>
The four separate explosions, undertaken on Salisbury Plain,
southern England, was the first public demonstration that it was
carrying out its obligations under the Ottawa Convention banning
anti-personnel mines.
</P>
<P>
British Defense Secretary George Robertson was quoted by
Reuters as saying Monday, "The world will be a safer place if
other countries take the same path and I encourage them to do so."
</P>
<P>
Britain pledged it would destroy its stockpile of 1 million
landmines by January 1, 2000, five years before the Ottawa
Convention deadline. 
</P>
</TEXT>
