<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Efforts in Drug Control Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 8 (Xinhua) -- China attaches great
importance to and is very much concerned about the comeback of
drugs in the country and has taken a series of firm
counter-measures.
</P>
<P>
This was expressed by Luo Gan, China's state councilor and
chairman of the Chinese delegation to the 20th Special Session of
the U.N. General Assembly, which opened here Monday to discuss the
worldwide drug control strategy.
</P>
<P>
As a country which suffered greatly from the evil of drugs in
history, Luo said, the Chinese government will, as always, pay
attention to and strengthen the drug enforcement, and take a
multi-pronged approach to address the drug issue by legal,
political, administrative, economic, cultural, educational, and
other means.
</P>
<P>
China's National People's Congress has enacted anti-drug laws.
Its government has established a national-level drug control
coordinating agency, he said.
</P>
<P>
From 1991 to 1997, Chinese law enforcement organizations seized
a total of 26 tons of heroin smuggled in from the "Golden
Triangle" area, he said.
</P>
<P>
As one of the first countries in the world to exercise
control over precursor chemicals, China has been implementing
the export license system covering the 22 U.N.-listed controlled
chemicals since 1993 and the import license system since 1996.
From 1991 to 1997, Chinese law enforcement organs seized a total
of 923 tons of precursor chemicals bound for the "Triangle" area
through smuggling.
</P>
<P>
Luo said that the Chinese government has always attached
importance to international drug control cooperation, stood for a
joint effort by all countries, and supported and taken active part
in the international fight against drugs. He cited a number of
U.S. activities against drugs China has participated in for the
past years.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, despite world's efforts in drug control, drug
production and trafficking will remain a worldwide problem for a
long time to come. It cannot be fundamentally resolved unless
all nations make concerted efforts and consolidate and develop
international drug control cooperation continuously.
</P>
<P>
He urged the international community to share responsibilities
and deal with the drug problem in an all-round manner. He also
assured the international organization China's cooperation and
continued contributions to eradicating illegal drugs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
