<HEADLINE> Space Shuttle Undocks From Mir Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Space shuttle
Discovery undocked from Russia's Mir space station Monday, thus
completing the ninth but also the last shuttle-Mir linkup program.
</P>
<P>
The separation of the two space stations marked the end of the
first phase of the U.S.-Russian space cooperation, and the
transition to the second phase -- the international space station.
</P>
<P>
In the last gathering in the space station, astronauts from the
two countries exchanged handshakes and embraced each other before
closing the hatches between the two spacecraft, 240 miles above
southern Russia.
</P>
<P>
Discovery is due to fly back and land at Florida's Kennedy
Space Station Friday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. space shuttle first docked with the Mir station in
1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
