<DOCNO> XIE19980609.0042 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pursuit for Peace Remains Major Task of Africa: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General Salim Ahmed
Salim of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) Monday called on
the African countries and peoples to keep their common and strong
determination to promote understanding and peace.
</P>
<P>
Citing the Ethiopian-Eritrean conflict which escalated over
the past few days, the secretary-general said that the African
peoples have been daily paying the heavy price of peace.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the 34th OAU Summit which opened here Monday,
Salim said that experiences show that peace is fragile and needs
to be constantly nurtured.
</P>
<P>
"The most recent and poignant case in point is the unfortunate
dispute which erupted between Ethiopia and Eritrea, which besides
being a shocking development, constitutes a major setback," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The secretary-general, nevertheless, expressed his belief that
the summit will in the end find the most appropriate way of
contributing to easing the tension and promoting a peaceful
solution to the dispute.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the African people need and deserve peace
more than anything else, and this quest for peace must be the
commitment of every African.
</P>
<P>
The secretary-general attributed the causes of conflicts in
Africa to ethnic divisions and polarization, non-respect for
human rights and the unequitable distribution of resources.
</P>
<P>
In order to solve these conflicts, it is imperative to make
use of the conflict prevention, management and resolution
mechanisms and strengthen them, he said.
</P>
<P>
Salim expressed the hope that the current summit will mark the
formal adoption and signature of the protocol on the
establishment of an African court on human and peoples' rights
which had been recommended by the just-ended OAU Council of
Ministers meeting.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the on-going global adjustments and the fast
development of new technologies, Salim warned that Africa could
find itself out of the new international environment, if it
failed to adjust to the new realities.
</P>
<P>
He called on African countries to work together within the
framework of the African Economic Community (AEC) which African
leaders have decided to establish to promote the socio-economic
recovery and development of the continent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
