Arafat Sunday and he had been expected to attend the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) summit in Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
As the sole consensus presidential candidate of Nigeria's five
political parties, Abacha was expected to transform himself
into a civilian president in the election scheduled for August 1,
this year.
</P>
<P>
Abacha, 54, took the leadership of Africa's most populous
country in November 1993. 
