<HEADLINE> Israel Responsible for Peace Process Deadlock: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 8 (Xinhua) -- President of Palestine, Yasser
Arafat, Monday morning once again strongly criticised Israel for
placing obstacles and impediments on the road of peace in the
middle east.
</P>
<P>
Israel is fully responsible for the impasse of the peace
process and for the failure of the international efforts,
especially the European, the Russian, the American and the Arab
efforts, Yasser Arafat said
in his address to the 34th summit of the Organization of African
Unity (OAU) which opened here Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
Refusing the offer of a chair and insisting on standing during
his speech, the somewhat tired Palestinian leader listed in the
strongest tone the various ways, means, tactics and plots used by
the Israeli government, such as closures, blockades and
suffocation, in an attempt to paralyze the Palestinian economy
and hinder the process of development and construction which the
Palestinian people began from zero.
</P>
<P>
Despite all these, the Palestinian side still adhered to
peace, he said. "We accepted the American ideas and proposals...
as well as the invitation to Washington, but until now, the
Israeli side still refuses the American proposals," he added.
</P>
<P>
Arafat also urged international community to assist the
Palestinian people in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
"Making peace in the region is a Palestinian--Israeli--Arab
interest and necessity but it is an international interest and
our peoples attach great hopes and aspirations on this peace," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his welcome to the Franco-Egyptian call for
convening an international conference that will help to rescue
and get the peace process out from its grave deadlock.
</P>
<P>
