<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High Court Rules Drug Dealers with Guns in Car </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A federal law adding five years
to the prison sentence of anyone carrying a gun while dealing in
illegal drugs can apply to those who keep a gun locked in a car's
glove compartment or trunk, the U.S. Supreme Court ruled on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The decision made the law a more potent weapon in Congress' war
on drugs, and could affect thousands of federal cases each year.
</P>
<P>
Drug traffickers arrested while in or near their cars can be
convicted of carrying a gun even if it is not immediately
accessible, the justices ruled in two cases from rural Louisiana
and Boston.
</P>
<P>
"The generally accepted contemporary meaning of the word
'carry' includes the carrying of a firearm in a vehicle," Justice
Stephen G. Breyer wrote for the court.
</P>
<P>
In an unanimous 1995 decision, the Supreme Court said
Prosecutors cannot invoke the "use" facet of the law unless they
show "active employment of the firearm." Just having a gun nearby
in case of a confrontation is not enough to be in violation of the
use provision, the justices ruled then.
</P>
<P>
But Breyer's opinion for the court said someone does "carry" a
gun when transporting it in his or her car.
</P>
<P>
Chief Justice William H. Rehnquist and other three justices
dissented. Writing for the four, Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg, said
the court "should leave it to Congress to speak in language that
is clear and definite if the Legislature wishes to impose the
sterner penalty."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980609.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills 12 in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 people have been
killed and an equal number of others seriously injured in a
disastrous road accident in which a taxi crashed head-on into a
trailer Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The injured were immediately admitted at Iganga hospital.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at Walugogo valley along the
Jinja-Iganga road during a heavy downpour at 4:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
The taxi was reported to be traveling from Iganga to Jinja
when it dashed into the trailer running in the opposite direction
before plunging into a swamp.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan government has recently blamed the poor
conditions of roads damaged by torrential rains brought by the
El-Nino weather pattern for the sharp rise of road accidents.
</P>
<P>
Taxis in Uganda are mini-buses often overloaded against their
capacities. They are often seen running at high speed along main
and feeder roads across the country, constituting another factor
leading to frequent disastrous road accidents.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, there are no restrictions whatever in Kampala which
forbid drivers from excessive drinking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
