<HEADLINE> U.S. Condemns Coup Attempt in Guinea-Bissau </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The United States on Monday
condemned a coup attempt by rebels of Guinea-Bisasu's troops to
overthrow the present government.
</P>
<P>
"The United States deplored and condemns the attempted coup
by elements of Guinea-Bissau's armed forces against the
democratically elected government," State Department spokesman
James Rubin said at a regular briefing.
</P>
<P>
"We urge all parties to guarantee the safety of civilians and
foreigners living in Guinea-Bissau," Rubin said. "We call upon
the rebels to return to their barracks and allow the government
to resume normal operations."
</P>
<P>
Heavy weapons fire resounded on Monday around part of
Guinea-Bissau's capital, where the rebels are entrenched in a
military complex, witnesses said. 
</P>
