<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Produces 1 Million Tons of Animal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Vice-Minister of
Agriculture Getachew Teklemedhin said Monday that the country can
produce 1,695,000 tons of animal products and by-products yearly.
</P>
<P>
In his speech at a parliament meeting which is discussing a
proclamation providing for the establishment of animal, animal
products and by-products marketing authority, the vice-minister
said Ethiopia has the potential to produce 1,200,000 hides and
skins which are the highest hard currency earners next to coffee.
</P>
<P>
He said the country has not benefited much from its huge
animal resource due to lack of relevant technology, effective
marketing system and sufficient quarantine stations.
</P>
<P>
The new policy of market economy has encouraged more
entrepreneurs to engage in poultry and cattle fattening as well
as animal products and by-products processing industries, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The marketing authority will facilitate the marketing
condition for individuals and organizations engaged in animal,
animal products and by-products trade activities, said Getachew
Teklemedhin.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian has the largest population of domestic animals in
Africa with the number of 130 million. Hides and skins are the
second largest hard currency earner next to coffee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
