<HEADLINE> U.S. Navy Secretary Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Navy Secretary John Dalton
resigned Monday after serving five years in the post, the White
House said.
</P>
<P>
"It is with a deep sense of gratitude that I accept the
resignation today of John Dalton as secretary of the Navy," U.S.
President Bill Clinton said in a statement issued by the White
House.
</P>
<P>
The president did not mention the reason of Delton's
resignation and a White House spokesman said he was unaware of the
reason.
</P>
<P>
Dalton, 56, a Naval Academy graduate who served as a submarine
officer during the Vietnam War era, was appointed as the secretary
by President Clinton in 1993. He was active in state and national
Democratic politics before the appointment.  
</P>
