<HEADLINE> Luo Gan Meets with British Deputy Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Luo Gan, State Counsellor
and head of the Chinese delegation attending the Special Session
of the General Assembly of the United Nations on World Drug
Problem, on Monday held talks with British Deputy Prime Minister
John Prescott on bilateral relations and international issues of
great importance.
</P>
<P>
Luo Gan said China has always attached great importance to the
development of relations with Britain, and to develop the long-term
and stable bilateral relations on the basis of mutual respect and
mutual benefit contributes not only to the interests of the two
countries, but also to the world' peace, stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Luo said the successful settlement of the Hong Kong issue
opened a new era for the development of the relations between the
two countries, and he believed that the exchange of visits
between the heads of the two states this year would further
promote the relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Prescott expressed satisfaction over the
settlement of the Hong Kong issue and the improvement of the
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said Britain appreciates the achievements China has made in
economy, and his country is willing to further promote the
cooperation between the two states in the areas of economy and
trade, drug control and environmental protection.  
</P>
