<HEADLINE> State STE Leading Group Holds First Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The state leading group for
promoting China's science, technology and education today
approved a development plan initiated by the Chinese Academy of
Sciences (CAS).
</P>
<P>
The group, led by Premier Zhu Rongji, also drew up an agenda
for implementing the national strategy of "revitalizing the
country with science, technology and education" in the year.
</P>
<P>
The group has been established by the Chinese government to
lead and coordinate the enhancement work for sciences and
technology.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin pledged early this year to support the
CAS plan and encouraged the Chinese researchers to face challenges
of the coming 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"We must work out an overall plan for the development of
science and technology and education in tandem with the growth of
national economy," Premier Zhu said at the group's first meeting,
which was attended by the group's deputy chief and Vice-Premier Li
Lanqing and other members of the group.
</P>
<P>
"The state will financially aid the plan and invest more money
in the science and technology and education endeavor," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the group members decided to hold a national
meeting for boosting the CAS plan throughout the whole
country. The third national work conference for education is also
on the list of the agenda.
</P>
<P>
The leading group is determined to guide the development of
science and technology and education while deepening the reform in
the field.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Lilan, Minister of Science and Technology, and Chen Zhili,
Minister of Education, separately reported their work at the
meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
