<HEADLINE> 11th International Tchaikovsky Competition Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The 11th International Tchaikovsky
Music Competition opened here on Tuesday with more than 500 young
musicians from 50 countries and regions taking part in the
competition.
</P>
<P>
The contestants will compete for titles in violin, cello, piano
and vocal music.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony was held in front of The P. I. Tchaikovsky
Conservatory of Music. More than 60 musicians from the Central
Academic Orchestra of the Russian Defense Ministry gave a
performance.
</P>
<P>
The International Tchaikovsky competition is believed to be the
most famous and prestigious music competition in the world.
</P>
<P>
Nineteen musicians from China's mainland and Taiwan are
participating in the competition.
</P>
<P>
The first competition was held in 1958, with 61 participants
from 22 countries.
</P>
<P>
Throughout the 40-year history of the International Tchaikovsky
Competition, nine Chinese musicians have won prizes. They include
pianists Liu Shikun and Yin Chengzong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
