<HEADLINE> Pele Leads All Stars of 20th Century World Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The World Team of Twentieth Century,
selected by some 250 football journalists around the world and an
international panel, has been announced here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 20th century squad is led by Pele, the greatest player of
all time and also features Diego Maradona, Johan Cruyff and Michel
Platini, now the co-president of the French World Cup Organising
Committee.
</P>
<P>
The line up includs: Lev Yashin (Soviet Union) in goal; a
defence of Carlos Alberto (Brazil), Franz Beckenbauer (West
Germany), Bobby Moore (England), and Nilton Santos (Brazil); a
midfield consisting of Cruyff (Netherlands), Alfredo Di Stefano
(Argentina), and Platini, with Pele, Garrincha (Brazil) and
Maradona (Argentina) in attack. 
</P>
