<HEADLINE> Well-protected County Holds Tourism Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Tourism-promotion activities were
launched today in Pingyao, a well-protected ancient county in
north China's Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Pingyao has been a county town since 221 BC, when China was
first unified. There are well protected anticent town walls,
residences, stores, temples, streets and county government office.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the town was the birthplace of China's modern
commercial and banking business.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the cultural site was listed as one of the world
cultural heritages by the United Nations Educational, Scientific
and Cultural Organization (UNESCO).
</P>
<P>
The tourism-promotion activities will end on June 15.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, an antiques trading fair is being held in the
county. 
</P>
