<HEADLINE> Supreme People's Procuratorate Calls for Supervision from NPC Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Supreme People's Procuratorate
has recently issued a notice, calling on procuratorial bodies at
all levels to tighten their ties with members of the National
People's Congress (NPC) and encourage their supervision.
</P>
<P>
The notice says that the procuratorial bodies at all levels
should routinely report their work to members of the NPC, China's
top legislative body, invite them to inspect their daily
work and attend related forums.
</P>
<P>
It says that motions, suggestions and letters submitted by NPC
members will be listed into the agenda of the Superme People's
Procuratorate, which is also responsible for reporting the results
to the NPC members.
</P>
<P>
When the NPC members demand to meet with heads of the
procuratorial bodies, the prosecutor concerned should meet with
them timely, answer questions candidly, and listen to the
opinions modestly, according to the notice.
</P>
<P>
The notice says procuratorial bodies at all levels should
institute the connection with NPC members as a system and
designate special departments and personnels to be in charge of
the work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
