<HEADLINE> Ten People in Hainan Killed in Thunderstorms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- During the past two months, 10
people in China's southernmost Hainan Province were killed and 26
injured by lightning strikes during thunderstorms.
</P>
<P>
Lightning strikes caused by thunderstorms in the eastern part
of the island have damaged abundant public facilities, residential
buildings, and household electronic appliances, resulting in
economic losses of nearly one million yuan (120,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Local officials said that most of the victims were farmers who
didn't know how to protect themselves from lightning strikes. They
were stricken while working in fields or taking shelter under
trees. 
