<HEADLINE> 4 Killed, 12 Wounded in Philippine Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Four civilians were killed while 12
others, including two babies, were wounded Monday night in an
explosion in a remote village in a southern Philippine province, a
military report said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The military said a group of unidentified armed men lobbed
homemade bombs and strafed houses in the village of Magdaup in
Ipil town, Zamboanga del Sur province, late Monday night.
</P>
<P>
Recovered from the site were one unexploded homemade bomb and
several empty shells of M-14 and M-16 rifles, the military said.
</P>
<P>
Elements of the Army's 102nd Infantry Brigade and 33rd Infantry
Battalion have been sent to pursue the attackers.
</P>
<P>
The military said it is unknown whether the attack was
conducted by the Muslim extremist group of Abu Sayyaf which raided
Ipil town in April 1994, killing hundreds of villagers.
</P>
<P>
Abu Sayyaf is one of the two remaining Muslim groups still
fighting the government and operating in southern Mindanao. The
other is the rebel Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF). 
</P>
</TEXT>
