<HEADLINE> Indian Spy Hanged in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 9 (Xinhua) -- An Indian spy Tuesday was hanged
by the Pakistani authorities in the country's largest Punjab
province, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The man identified as Bilobir Singh was executed in the Sahiwal
jail in southern Punjab, about 400 km south of Islamabad, Tuesday
afternoon, the reports quoted jail officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
Singh was arrested on charges of spying nine years ago by the
Pakistani Army's Special Squad in a military area in Sahiwal. He
was later sentenced to death by a military court.
</P>
<P>
The Indian national, who was transferred to the Sahiwal jail
two years ago, had filed an appeal with the Pakistani president.
However, his appeal was rejected Tuesday. 
