<HEADLINE> China to Issue 2.1 Billion Yuan in Railway Construction Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- China will launch another bond
issue Wednesday to support its cash-strapped railway projects, as
another move to step up railroad construction and stimulate
national economic growth.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2.13 billion yuan (256.6 million US dollars) is
expected to be raised through the bond issue, which will be mainly
invested in the country's key railway projects.
</P>
<P>
The issue includes 530 million yuan (63.86 million US dollars)
in three-year bonds and 1.6 billion yuan (192.8 million US
dollars) in five-year bonds, with an annual interest rate of 8 and
8.6 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Guaranteed by the Ministry of Railways, the bond issue was
given an AAA-rating. China Securities Co. Ltd. will be the lead
underwriter of the bonds.
</P>
<P>
China aims to invest 245 billion yuan (29.5 billion US dollars)
in railway construction between 1998 and 2002, and increase the
total length of the railroads above 70,000 kilometers by the year
2002.
</P>
<P>
It also revised its 1998 investment plan for railway projects,
increasing the total amount to 45 billion yuan (5.4 billion US
dollars) from 34.9 billion yuan (4.2 billion US dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
