investments in Tunisia in the last 10 years stood at 3.2 billion
Tunis dinars (about 3 billion dollars), accounting for 9 percent
of the total foreign investments in the country during the period.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia was the the largest investor and Kuwait came the
second.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics, the Arab investments focused on
banking, tourism and agrarian projects, assisting the
establishment of 1,200 economic institutions and providing 80,000
jobs.
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- The latest official statistics have shown that
foreign banks in the United Arab Emirates (UAE) gained a 25
percent increase in the total profits compared to that in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The profit stood at 1.3 billion UAE dirhams (about 354 million
dollars). The British Bank, the oldest foreign bank in the UAE,
took the lead as it gained a third of the total profit. 
