<HEADLINE> Russia Ready to Train Indonesian Cosmonauts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Russia is ready to provide training
for Indonesia's would-be cosmonauts as part of its efforts to
strengthen bilateral ties with Indonesia, a Russian envoy said
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We are ready to train Indonesian cosmonauts and fly them into
the space," Russian Ambassador to Indonesia Nikolai N. Soloviev
said.
</P>
<P>
He said officials of the two countries had touched the matter
at bilateral talks sometime ago.
</P>
<P>
Soloviev said he realized that it is not an easy task to train
people to become cosmonauts but it is his government's commitment
to help the Indonesian people.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia itself once had two would-be astronauts and one of
them was Pratiwi Sudarmono, who was to be sent to space in
cooperation with the U.S. National Aeronautics and Space
Administration.
