<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> African States Called to Harmonize Industrial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- African leaders have called on
all member states of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) to
ensure the harmonization of their industrial development plans
with the alliance for Africa's industrialization in a bid to
promote continental economic integration.
</P>
<P>
At the on-going three-day OAU summit scheduled to close
Wednesday, the leaders Tuesday requested member states to create or
strengthen consultative mechanisms between the government and the
private sector.
</P>
<P>
This should be done with the view to formulating industrial
development policies and strategies in line with the objectives
of their economic and social development plans as well as
programs for regional and sub-regional economic integration and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The leaders said that OAU member states should also create
favorable conditions to enable the private sectors in Africa to
play a more important role in the industrialization of African
countries.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, they agreed that member states should restructure
the public sector to enable it to improve its performance,
modernize its management and stimulate competitiveness in order
to be in a position to assist the private sector in its
industrialization endeavor.
</P>
<P>
The leaders at the OAU summit also requested member states to
implement industrial development, cooperation and integration
policies and strategies in Africa at national, sub-regional and
regional levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
