<DOCNO> XIE19980609.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Becomes Largest Market for Israeli Communications Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Rapid growth in China's information
industry and a huge demand for high-tech products have turned the
country into the largest market for the major Israeli data
communications business.
</P>
<P>
Reuven Eliaz, spokesman for RAD Data Communications, said
recently that China will, according to the original projection,
assume its present position in 2000 or 2001. "It seems we were
too conservative about the Chinese market," he said.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year, RAD's sales in China
reached 9 million U.S. dollars. And its sales this year is
expected to increase by 58 percent compared with the 1997 figure,
1.5 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to Zohar Zisapel, chairman of the board for RAD who
came here recently with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu,
traditional markets for Israel's communications industry are the
United States and Germany.
</P>
<P>
He said that last year China surpassed Germany as RAD's second
biggest market, accounting for 22 percent of RAD's total sales,
only 1 percent less than the United States.
</P>
<P>
Industry analysts say that, while RAD is not as well-known as
some competitors in developed countries, its stable performance
and the low price of its products have won Chinese carriers.
</P>
<P>
They say China's communication sector, especially the
telecommunications sector that has the most RAD involvement, is
relative young, and the carriers are very conscious of
cost-efficiency.
</P>
<P>
As part of RAD's further commitment to China, Eliaz announced,
RAD will introduce to China its voice/data communications solution
-- MAXcess products later this month.
</P>
<P>
MAXcess involves technology such as voice compression and frame
relay, and offers simultaneous data, voice and fax services.
</P>
<P>
The sales volume of RAD in 1997 was 138 million dollars, 97
percent of which was from overseas sales. The increase over last
year is expected to be 20-to-30 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
