<HEADLINE> India to Import 2 Million Tons of Wheat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government has decided
to import 2 million tons of wheat in the current financial year to
make up for a shortfall in domestic production, a cabinet minister
said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken after reviewing the status of wheat
production in the 1997-98 harvest season, Minister of State for
Food and Consumer Affairs Satya Pal Singh Yadav told the Indian
Parliament in a written reply.
</P>
<P>
India produced some 195 million tons of grain in the 1997-98
financial year, 5 million tons less than the set target of 200
million tons.
</P>
<P>
According to initial estimates by the Ministry of Agriculture,
India would produce 64.51 million tons of wheat in 1997-98 as
against 69.27 million tons in the previous year. 
</P>
