<HEADLINE> OAU to Contribute to African Economic Community's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The African Economic Community
(AEC), established last year for the continent's economic
integration, is expected to get financial resources from the
Organization of African Unity (OAU).
</P>
<P>
At the current 34th AOU summit, African heads of state and
government have decided that a minimum of 10 percent of OAU's
regular budget should be set aside to finance the activities of
the community.
</P>
<P>
Detailed budget of AEC will be produced by the general
secretariat of the community later.
</P>
<P>
The leaders also requested the general secretariat to take
account of the on-going restructuring of OAU and streamline the
activities of the community as a way of achieving efficiency in
resource utilization.
</P>
<P>
The community should also maintain close cooperation with the
United Nations Economic Commission on Africa, African Development
Bank and regional economic communities in order to pool resources
and enhance cost-effectiveness.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the general secretariat is urged by the leaders to
undertake a study on self-financing mechanisms for the community
and regional economic communities across the continent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
