<HEADLINE> Bomb Hoax Creates Panic at U.S. embassy in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A bomb hoax created panic among
diplomats and staff at the U.S. Embassy here Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
American diplomats and Pakistani staff at the embassy had to
evacuate the building after the embassy's telephone exchange
received a call from an unidentified person at around 2:45 p.m.
(local time), saying a bomb had been placed in the embassy.
</P>
<P>
Embassy officials immediately informed the Islamabad Police
Control. Emergency sirens were sounded in the embassy and local
police blocked all the roads leading to it.
</P>
<P>
Police and a bomb disposal squad rushed to the embassy and
carried out a thorough search but did not find any bomb after two
hours of effort. 
