<HEADLINE> Luanda's First 19 State Firms Privatized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The first 19 state-owned
enterprises in Luanda Province have been privatized in accordance
with the 1998-2000 industrial development plan.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises, all medium-and-small sized enterprises in
trade, hotel industry are the first of the 80 enterprises to be
privatized this year, said Ramos Rodrigues, Executive Secretary
of the Enterprise Reform Committee.
</P>
<P>
Luanda Governor, Anibal Rocha, said recently that the aim of
privatization of state enterprises is to strengthen their
competitiveness, raise their efficiency, and make them turn out
more products and service.
</P>
<P>
The privatization could also offer more job opportunities for
the demobilized soldiers in the peace process, he said.
</P>
<P>
With the deepening of the privatization process, he said,
supervision organs should strengthen their work to ensure that
the state gets tax and fair competition among enterprises.
</P>
<P>
According to the 1998-2000 privatization plan, all the
state-owned enterprises should be privatized, with 40 percent
being privated this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
