<HEADLINE> Senior Official Li Lanqing Visits Anti-drug Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- While visiting an anti-drug
exhibition here Monday evening, Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
stressed that youngsters should be taught to know the hazard of
drugs and resist drugs on their own.
</P>
<P>
Touring the exhibition halls, Li was told that more than 80
percent of drug takers were youngsters, most of whom got addicted
to drug-taking without knowing the hazard of drugs.
</P>
<P>
Li is also a standing committee member of the central committee
of the Chinese Communist Party. He noted that youngsters are the
future and hope of the nation and should be taught to know the
hazard of drugs and stay away from drugs.
</P>
<P>
He urged various anti-drug departments to take different
educational measures with regard to youngsters of different ages
and make them foster strong anti-drug awareness.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, sponsored by the Ministry of Public Security,
has received strong responses from the masses. Since its opening
on May 29, the exhibition has attracted more than 130,000
visitors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
