<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Slide on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to slide
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index (STII) lost 11.36 points to close at 1117.21 on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Shares were weaker at the close of a quiet session Tuesday
compared with that on Monday when STII lost nearly 40 points.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the market lost ground amid a flurry of selling by
foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
The advance in early dealings sparked by Monday's news of
banking reform was short-lived, they said.
</P>
<P>
Concerns over the regional currency crisis continued to weaken
sentiment, they noted.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume recovered to 113.577 million units,
valued at 253.48 million Singapore dollars (about 148.53 million
U.S. dollars). There were 131 rises against 142 falls while 318
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Easyknit was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 13.298 million units. It was followed by TAC 200 which
had 10.776 million shares traded. DBS Land was next with 9.88
million shares changed hands.
</P>
