<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Director of Home
Affairs Shelley Lau will lead a delegation of 12 Provisional
District Board (PDB) chairmen and several government officials to
Singapore on a four-day visit as off Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The visit is aimed to exchange views and experience with
Singaporean government officials and community leaders on private
building management, community building at the district level and
ways to mobilize community support in promoting a healthy living
culture.
</P>
<P>
The study tour would allow the PDB chairmen to gain insights
from a successful city with many similarities to Hong Kong, Lau
said.
</P>
