<HEADLINE> Indonesian to Investigate Officials' Wealth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The office of Indonesia's attorney
general has formed a team to investigate the wealth of present and
former Indonesian government officials, a spokesman of the office
said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The result (of the investigations) of officials of both
central and provincial governments will be announced to the
public," Spokesman Barman Zahir said.
</P>
<P>
He said the team will be led by the junior attorney general for
civil and state administrative courts. He did not say when the
results of the investigations will be announced.
</P>
<P>
The offices of the attorney general, chief public prosecutor
and public prosecutor have asked the public to provide information
about the wealth of officials to help the team in its
investigations, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Attorney General Soedjono C. Atmonegoro said last week that the
government has started an investigation into the wealth of former
government officials, including former President Soeharto and his
family. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
