<HEADLINE> Eritrea Accuses Ethiopia for Fresh Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- As African leaders are trying
to find a way to solve the ever escalating crisis between
Ethiopia and Eritrea, the two conflicting sides have not ceased
accusing each other for attacks.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release available here Tuesday morning
which is circulating at the on-going 34th assembly of heads of
state and government of the Organization of African Unity (OAU),
the Ethiopian army launched a fresh attack on Eritrean positions
in the Zalambesa area, a 400 km triangle which both countries
claim, at around 05:15 a.m. Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has been stepping up preparations for this attack
since last Thursday when it publicly announced that it has given
orders to the country's armed forces to take action against
Eritrea, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Eritrea said in the
press release.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian attack came only a day after Eritrea renewed
its call at the OAU summit in Ouagadougou, capital of
Burkina Faso, for the cessation of all hostilities and the start
of direct talks in the presence of high level mediators, the
press release said.
</P>
<P>
The government of Eritrea describes this fresh attack as
another proof that Ethiopia is bent on war.
</P>
<P>
The press release further said that Ethiopia had unleashed
five attacks in the past two weeks, and virtually imposed a
blockade of Eritrea's air space and port activities by
threatening to attack commercial aircraft entering the country as
well as civilian vessels calling at the Eritrean ports of Assab
and Massawa bordering the Red Sea.
</P>
<P>
While reiterating its call for a cessation of hostilities, the
Eritrean government affirms that it has no option, but to confront
these attacks resolutely in order to defend its sovereignty and
territorial integrity, the release said.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia-Eritrea conflict has been top on the agenda both at
the 68th OAU ministers' meeting and the on-going 34th
OAU summit. African ministers and heads of state and government
have all expressed their concern over the conflict and special
sessions have been held one after another concerning the
conflict.
</P>
<P>
Despite the ever escalating conflict between the two countries
and the ever heated-up diplomatic wars between the two sides
within the conference center here, leaders are working hard to
persuade the two sides to exert the utmost restraint while trying
to find an appropriate solution.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
