<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Condemns Massive Displacement of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Foreign Ministry
said Tuesday that the Eritrean authorities have expelled over
3,000 Ethiopians from Eritrea and detained 530 others.
</P>
<P>
In a press release issued here, the Ethiopian Foreign Ministry
said, "Two thousand were herded in different parts of Eritrea,
their belongings confiscated and driven out of the country in the
most inhuman manner."  "One thousand more were evicted
empty-handed from Assab (a eastern city bordering the Red Sea)
alone and 530 others have been detained," it added.
</P>
<P>
The ministry calls on the international community to condemn
"this massive displacement of innocent civilians as a flagrant
violation of human rights."
</P>
<P>
"Ethiopia is gravely concerned that the action of the Eritrean
authority is consistent with their objective of inciting
animosity between the peoples of the two countries," it said.
</P>
<P>
"Unless pressure is brought to bear on the Eritrean
authorities, they will not desist from committing more atrocities
against civilian Ethiopian citizens residing in Eritrea," said
the ministry in the press release. 
</P>
