<HEADLINE> German Unemployment Rate Down in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Economic recovery drove jobless rate
in Germany down to 10.9 percent in May from 11.4 percent in April,
and made it the first year-on-year decline in nearly three years.
</P>
<P>
In May 1997, German jobless rate was 11.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
As shown in the latest report released by the Federal Labor
Office in Nuremberg, Germany's jobless dropped by seasonally
adjusted 60,000 to about 4.324 million last month.
</P>
<P>
In western area of the country, the adjusted number of people
out of work fell by 30,000 to 2.912 million, while the number of
those in the east was down by 30,000 to 1.412 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
