<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals in Sri Lanka Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in Sri Lanka in
the first four months this year have seen a 1.3 percent rise, a
tourist board spokesman said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the number of foreigners visiting the
country has increased to 130,341 from January to April this year
from 113,397 during the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Tourist arrivals from Western Europe recorded an 18.1 percent
increase, with visitors from Germany rising 20.7 percent, United
Kingdom 25.3 percent, France 5.8 percent, and Netherlands 68.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
He said Eastern Europe accounted for a 21.3 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
However, he added that the number of people visiting Sri Lanka
from the North American region has decreased by 8.4 percent,
Africa 56.3 percent, Middle East 29.4 percent, South Asia 27.8
percent and Australasia 13.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The tourist industry, one of the top foreign exchange earners,
has been recognized by the government as an essential industry for
the economic and social development of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan government has reportedly offered attractive
incentives for investors in a bid to further boost the industry.
</P>
<P>
Over 366,200 visitors arrived in Sri Lanka last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
