<HEADLINE> Heavy Rain Hits Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rain has hit Hong Kong
since early Tuesday morning, causing flooding in some areas and
forcing the canceling of school classes and some government
functions.
</P>
<P>
A black rainstorm warning signal was issued early Tuesday
morning, which means heavy rain is expected to fall generally over
Hong Kong exceeding 70 millimeters an hour and was likely to
continue.
</P>
<P>
By 10:00 a.m., the Drainage Services Department has received a
total of eight flooding cases throughout Hong Kong but no one was
injured in these incidents.
</P>
<P>
The Education Department announced that all bi-sessional
schools will be closed Tuesday morning and whole-day schools will
be closed all day due to heavy rain.
</P>
<P>
The Hospital Authority announced that its specialist clinics,
geriatric day hospitals and day hospitals will close but Accident
and Emergency services at hospitals will remain normal.
</P>
<P>
The Judiciary announced that because of the hoisting of black
rainstorm warning, all courts, tribunals, court registries and
offices was closed Tuesday morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
