<HEADLINE> Northern Chinese Province To Clean Up Haihe River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 9 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
plans to spend 16.5 billion yuan (1.98 billion US dollars) on
cleaning the Haihe River there in three to five years.
</P>
<P>
The section of the river in Hebei drains 172,970 square
kilometers of land, or 92.1 percent of Hebei.
</P>
<P>
The province will need 135 projects to deal with the pollution,
including nearly 100 sewage treatment plants and drinking water
protection projects in urban areas, according to the provincial
environmental protection bureau.
</P>
<P>
It will also need to dig 1,521 deep wells because of the
pollution of underground waters in some parts of the province.
</P>
<P>
The bureau report says that by year 2000, all the province's
industrial polluters will meet state-set pollution discharge
standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
