<HEADLINE> Profile: Nigeria's New Leader A. Abubakar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's former Chief of Defense
Staff, Major-General Abudusalam Abubakar has been inaugurated as
the country's new leader after the death of former head of state,
General Sani Abacha.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar was sworn in Tuesday morning in Nigerian capital
at the presidential villa Aso Rock, where the Provisional Ruling
Council reached an agreement on the new leadership at an emergency
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria's defense spokesman Colonel Godwin Ugbo has confirmed
the new development to Xinhua, when contacted in his office in
Lagos.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar was born on June 13, 1942, in Minna, capital of Niger
State in northern Nigeria. He came from the Hausa group, one the
three major ethnic groups in Nigeria, and believes in Islamism.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar was at different times the commander of the Nigerian
Army, 93th Battalion, commander of the Nigerian battalion in the
U.N. peace-keeping force in Lebanon, commander of the third and
ninth mechanized brigades, commander of the 82nd division and the
first mechanized division.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar was promoted to the rank of major-general in October
1990. He was appointed the Chief of Defense Staff in 1993 and has
been holding the position since then.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar's hobby includes squash, hockey, football and camera
shooting.
</P>
<P>
He was married to Amina Abubakar, a judge at the Abuja High
Court and has three daughters and two sons.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar has been promoted to the rank of general after he was
inaugurated as Nigeria's new leader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
