<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Escalation of Conflict Between Ethiopia, Eritrea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese government feels regret for
the escalation of the Ethiopia-Eritrea conflict, Foreign Ministry
spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here today.
</P>
<P>
In response to a reporter's question, Zhu said China, as a
friendly country of both Ethiopia and Eritrea, sincerely hopes the
two countries will realize ceasefire immediately and settle their
disputes in a peaceful manner and through negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Maintaining good-neighborly relationship between Ethiopia and
Eritrea is not only in the interest of the two countries' national
development but also conducive to stability and security in this
region, he noted.
</P>
<P>
In order to ensure safety of Chinese citizens, Zhu said, the
Chinese government has evacuated temporarily Chinese business
people and part of Chinese embassy staff from Eritrea. 
