<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Foreign Minister Arrives in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan Foreign Minister
Lakshman Kadiragamar arrived here Tuesday on a two-day official
visit in connection with the 10th summit of the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC).
</P>
<P>
He told the press at the airport upon arrival that "the visit
is purely to hand over formal invitation letter from Sri Lankan
President Mrs. Kumaratunga to Prime Minister of Nepal Girija
Prasad Koirala to attend the 10th SAARC summit to be held in
Colombo, Sri Lanka next month."
</P>
<P>
He said that his visit is not a bilateral one but "a SAARC
visit."
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister has visited Bangladesh and India on his
current tour of the SAARC capitals to hand over invitation letters
to the 10th summit to be held on July 9-11.
</P>
<P>
In reply to a question, he said that the summit does not have
any agenda. "The summit adopts various reports prepared by the
bodies which are below the summit and there is no formal agenda, "
he added.
</P>
<P>
SAARC, formed in December 1985, aims to establish a South Asian
Free Trade Area preferably by the year 2001.
</P>
<P>
It now groups Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives, Nepal,
Pakistan and Sri Lanka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
