<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Frenchmen Ready for World Cup But No Dupes: Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Frenchmen are ready to make the
football World Cup a great success but are fully aware of the
commercial interests involving principal sponsors in the games,
said a poll published by the daily Humanite on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The poll was conducted by the CSA polling institute among 1,004
 people above the age of 18 at the request of the newspaper and
the city of Saint-Denis, where the Stadium of France is located.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-nine percent of the people polled said that the World
Cup is linked with money, while from 47 to 60 percent said it is
connected with drug, violence, cheating, and corruption.
</P>
<P>
Ninety percent said the World Cup will be a great media show,
87 percent said it is a great popular festival, while 56 percent
consider it an event which should not be missed.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-three percent said that whether the World Cup is a
success should be judged through the way of receiving visitors by
the French people, far more than 13 percent who think that the
festivals organized during the season are the most important.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-one percent said television is the best way of watching
the event, against 28 percent who said they will join the
festivals organized in their cities.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-six percent said they will do all to hide away from the
event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
