<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Wheat Output Hits Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's wheat production
surpassed all the previous records with over 1.8 million tons
harvested this year, about 350,000 tons more than that of last
year, press reports said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ever highest production of wheat this year was attributed
to the expansion of cultivated acreage, increase in per-acre yield
and favorable weather, the reports quoted official sources as
saying.
</P>
<P>
About 70,000 hectares of land was brought under wheat
cultivation this year, which was 14 percent more than that of the
previous year. On the other hand, per hectare-yield increased by
nine percent to 2,265 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh is an agriculture-based country with rice as its
major cereal crop.
</P>
<P>
Owing to some incentive measures taken by the government in
recent years, wheat yield increased with national wheat area
expanding rapidly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
