<HEADLINE> Russia's Statistics Chief Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Head of Russia's State Committee for
Statistics (SCS) Yuri Yurkov was arrested Monday night for
allegedly distorting statistics to help big companies evade tax.
</P>
<P>
Also arrested was a leader of the statistics house's computer
center, Itar-Tass news agency said in a report.
</P>
<P>
They were charged of systematically distorting statistical data
on big firms and companies, enabling the firms to dodge tax
payments, a government official was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The case was handled by the Federal Security Service and the
Office for Prosecutor-General. Yurkov has been reportedly under
investigation and field surveillance since April.
</P>
<P>
It was believed to be the first criminal case against such
high-ranking officials in several years.
</P>
<P>
Yurkov was appointed head of the SCS in October 1993. 
</P>
