<HEADLINE> Pakistan Sends More Relief Goods to Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan on Tuesday despatched 14
trucks carrying essential food stuff for earthquake-victims in
northern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The trucks are ferrying 100 tons of rice, wheat, sugar and
pulses and 50 tons of ghee to earthquake-hit areas between Takhar
and Badakhshan provinces of Afghanistan, said the Ministry of
Foreign Affairs, according to the official Associated Press of
Pakistan.
</P>
