<HEADLINE> Chinese Exhibition in Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese exposition in the city of
Lisbon is giving people there a taste of ancient civilization and
high-tech development.
</P>
<P>
China is displaying its early maritime culture and present use
of marine science and technology at the '98 World Exposition,
whose theme is "Sea-Heritage of the Future," using audio-video
equipment.
</P>
<P>
China has one of the biggest exhibits at the international
event, which started late last month, with a floor field of 1,620
square meters,
</P>
<P>
Cui Yushan, the head of the delegation and vice-president of
the China Council for the Promotion of International Trade, says
that many visitors have been impressed with China's navigation
technology in ancient times as well as by its modern science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
The exposition has 160 countries and international
organizations participating. Its purpose is to help people learn
more about the sea and to encourage them to work for an ecological
balance and the healthy development of society. 
</P>
