<HEADLINE> Chinese, Italian Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, in a meeting
with his Italian counterpart Oscar Luigi Scalfaro here today, said
that China is ready to make a joint effort with Italy to establish
a long-term and stable Sino-Italian relationship of friendship and
cooperation oriented towards the next century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the Chinese government has always treasured
Sino-Italian relations and has worked to improve them and said he
believes that Scalfaro's China visit will help mutual
understanding and promote Sino-Italian relations.
</P>
<P>
China and Italy have ancient civilizations and a long history
of mutual exchanges, and those relations have developed smoothly
with the increase in exchanges of high-level visits and have made
remarkable progress in cooperation in various fields since the two
opened diplomatic ties, he said.
</P>
<P>
Italy is a major European country that is playing an
increasingly important role in European and international affairs,
Jiang said, and although China and Italy have different national
conditions, social systems, culture traditions and economic
development, they have no fundamental conflict of interest, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"We are moving towards a multi-polarized world and Asia and
Europe are trying to establish a new partnership, so improved
Sino-Italian cooperation not only serves the two nations, it also
is in the interest of world peace, stability and development,"
Jiang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
