<HEADLINE> 11 Killed, 17 Wounded in Bus Accident in E. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean police confirmed that 11
people died Monday when a long distance bus collided with an
18-ton truck 116 km from Mutare in east Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Assistant Inspector Eddison Makacha said that of the 26
passengers aboard, eight people died on the spot and 17 were
injured, the Zimbabwe News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the eight who were seriously injured, two died on arrival
at Birchenough Bridge and Chipinge District hospitals, while the
third person died on the way to Mutare General Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Although investigations were in progress, said Makacha, it
appeared that the driver of the bus encroached into the right
lane resulting in the bus ramming into the trailer of the lorry.
</P>
<P>
This is the second bus disaster in Manicaland Province this
year. In January, 41 people died on the spot and 64 others were
injured in a bus accident. 
</P>
