<HEADLINE> International Agricultural Development Loans In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The International Fund for
Agricultural Development (IFAD) had provided China with 315
million U.S. dollars in agricultural project loans by the end of
1997.
</P>
<P>
The projects helped 1.7 million poor farmers live a better life
through farmland reclamation.
</P>
<P>
Through the use of these funds, two counties in Hebei Province
were able to improve 9,000 ha of saline and alkali land and turn
9,000 ha. of arid land into irrigated fields, and build forest
zones and orchards on 5,000 ha. of wasteland. As a result, the
annual income of farmers in 238 villages in the two counties
has doubled.
</P>
<P>
IFAD has provided 5.65 billion U.S. dollars worth of loans for
111 developing countries in the construction of 489 projects, as
well as 200 million U.S. dollars worth of technical aids over the
past two decades. More than 80 percent of these loans have been
used in 83 nations. 
</P>
