<HEADLINE> Outstanding Overseas-Financed Businesses in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The north China city of Tianjin
selected 105 overseas-financed companies for their outstanding
business performance on Monday.
</P>
<P>
They include Motorola Tianjin Co. Ltd., Yamaha Tianjin
Co. Ltd., and Sino-French Dynasty Co. Ltd. Twenty-three of the
companies were also given the title of best overseas-financed
enterprise for 1997.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has approved 11,500 overseas-backed businesses, with
contracts worth about 20 billion U.S. dollars. Paid-in overseas
investment amounts to 8.2 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-financed businesses now contribute 40 percent of
Tianjin's industrial output value, 55 percent of its profits, and
30 percent of its taxes, and have created 300,000 job
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to these overseas-financed businesses, Tianjin has had
an average growth of 20 percent in foreign trade over the past
five years, and half of its exports come from overseas-backed
companies. 
