<HEADLINE> China's Shipping Sector Improving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 9 (Xinhua) -- China's container shipping
business has begun to show signs of a rebound, according to the
Shanghai Shipping Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The index released last week was 1028.15, up 1.3 percent from
May.
</P>
<P>
As currencies were devalued in Asian countries recently, there
was a rapid increase of exports and shipping costs of Chinese
lines going to these countries rose.
</P>
<P>
The costs of shipping to Europe and the United States also rose
to some extent, but even though costs were up, analysts say that
unbalanced trade also ate away at some of the profit, and some
shippers had empty containers on part of the voyage because of
fewer imports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
