<HEADLINE> Japanese Head for France to Taste World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 9 (Xinhua) -- About 300 Japanese soccer fans left
Tokyo on Tuesday for France to taste the World Cup finals for
the first time with their national team.
</P>
<P>
It was the first major contingent of Japanese fans to head for
France in time for the opening of World Cup Finals on Wednesday,
local airline officials said.
</P>
<P>
Two Japanese Airlines plan to send a total of 40 extra flights
bound for Paris this week, the officials added.
</P>
<P>
Most seats on the flights have already been reserved, the
officials said.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-five thousand Japanese fans are flying to France to
support the Japanese team, more than double the number who went
to the 1996 Atlanta Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Japan is in Group H with Argentina, Croatia and Jamaica. They
kick off against Argentina in Toulouse on Sunday. 
