<HEADLINE> Chinese Company Builds Chinese Products Street In Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 9 (Xinhua) --A company from Harbin, the capital of
northereast China's Heilongjiang Province, has built a Chinese
Products Street in the port city of Nakhodka in the Far East
region of Russia.
</P>
<P>
The 300-meter-long street has been a center for business since
June 3 and now has 53 shops dealing in several thousand Chinese
commodities, ranging from garments, shoes, and headgear to food,
tobacco, alcohol, home appliances, handicrafts, and ceramics.
</P>
<P>
The street was built at a cost of 3 million U.S. dollars by the
Xuanyuan Enterprises Group, local sources say.
</P>
<P>
The day the street opened for business, the Harbin Economic and
Technological Development Zone signed an agreement with Nakhodka's
free trade zone and they reached a consensus on simplifying
customs clearance procedures and lower fees to ensure smooth
trade. 
