<HEADLINE> Nigeria's New Leader Appeals to "Move Nation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Niogeria's Chief of Defense Staff,
Major-General Abudusalam Abubakar has been inaugurated as the
country's new leader after the death of former head of state,
General Sani Abacha.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar was sworn in at about 2:30 a.m. Tuesday morning in
Nigerian capital at the presidential villa Aso Rock, where the
ruling Provisional Ruling Council reached an agreement on the new
leadership at an emergency meeting.
</P>
<P>
In a brief acceptance speech, Abubakar described his
appointment as a personal challenge, saying that "all hands must
be on deck to move this nation forward".
</P>
<P>
Abubakar said he will address the nation in due course, when
he is expected to make major policy announcement.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar has announced a seven-day national mourning in honor
of Abacha, during which flags will fly at half mast.
</P>
<P>
Abacha died of heart attack in the early hour of Monday and
was buried Monday night in his home town Kano in northern
Nigeria. 
</P>
