<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rodman Fined $10,000 by NBA for Bad Behavior </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Dennis Rodman was fined 10,000
U.S.-dollar by the NBA and probably will be fined by the Chicago
Bulls after missing practice and the mandatory NBA press
conference on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The tattooed and multihued NBA star, who had tripped to Las
Vegas to seek fun after the Finals Game 1, was seen Monday night
attending a wrestling match in a grand box.
</P>
<P>
He was with World Championship Wrestling president Eric
Bischoff and wrestlers Hulk Hogan.
</P>
<P>
"I talked to Dennis and he did not speak," the Bulls coach
Phil Jackson said. "He said to my assistant trainer he didn't
think he could make it down here in time for the press
conference. I asked him, 'Dennis, what should I say to the press?'
and he hung up on me."
</P>
<P>
"It's very frustrating at this time, " Scottie Pippen said.
"But you don't want to carry that into the next time, you don't
want to carry that into the next practice. You want the team
chemistry to stay as strong as possible. Especially the situation
we're in, we don't want Dennis taking the focus away from the
team."
</P>
<P>
Rodman dares to do anything. He waltzes in a half-hour later
for home games. He disappears to the locker room early in each
half -- supposedly to keep his muscles warm -- forcing Jackson to
send a trainer to fetch him as he can make a grand entrance.
</P>
<P>
"Dennis is not a normal person in our society, but he's great
in what he does here," said Jackson.
</P>
<P>
Rodman has been acting goofy for years, and the Bulls knew what
they were getting when they signed him three years ago. His latest
one-year contract was designed specifically to make him behave.
</P>
<P>
He has a 4.5 million U.S.-dollar base salary plus another 5.95
million dollars in games-played incentives and bonuses.
</P>
<P>
"With Dennis comes a lot of baggage," Michael Jordan said. "we
just have to carry it and we have to accept it."
</P>
<P>
But as long as Rodman performs well in the next game, the
Bulls perhaps won't do anything to upset him. So, wait and see
what the "worm" behaves on Wednesday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
