<HEADLINE> Southwestern Chinese Police Dismissed For Incompetence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- China's Guizhou Province dismissed
133 policemen who either violated the law or acted improperly in
doing their work by the end of May.
</P>
<P>
According to yesterday's People's Daily, public security
bureaus at different levels in the province began an investigation
of patrol police and traffic police departments, police
substations, houses of detention, and drug units.
</P>
<P>
They examined more than 10,000 cases that were dealt with over
the past several years and sent more than 20 groups of
plainchlothes police to investigate.
</P>
<P>
One policeman who was found to have taken 3,000 yuan worth of
bribes and cigarettes was dismissed and sentenced to two years in
prison, the paper reported.
</P>
<P>
Ninety-two other policemen who were found to have violated
various rules will also be dismissed. 
