<HEADLINE> Romania to Issue Euro Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Romania will issue five-year Euro
bonds soon, valued at 250 million U.S. dollars, the Financial
Ministry said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Two German investment banks will be responsible for the issue,
Minister of Finance Daniel Daianu said. The exact issue date had
yet to be decided on the situation of the international financial
markets.
</P>
<P>
Last year the Romanian Financial Ministry issued on the
European market 600 million five-year German Mark bonds, with an
interest of 7.75 percent.
</P>
<P>
At the end of last February, Romania had a total medium and
long term foreign debt of 8.29 billion U.S. dollars, including a
4.8 billion dollar public debt and a two billion dollar government
guaranteed debt, the Romanian National Bank said in a release.
</P>
<P>
