<HEADLINE> Over 152,000 Flee Indonesia During Riots in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Over 152,000 Indonesians and
foreigners from at least 47 countries fled the country during last
month's riots, a report published by the Ministry of Justice has
said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in the report that 70,837 Indonesians and
81,526 foreigners left Indonesia from airports and seaports in
Java, Bali and Sumatra, according to press reports Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The number of people leaving the country from Soekarno-Hatta
airport (in Jakarta) peaked on May 19, namely 17,212 people," the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,188 people died in rioting in Jakarta and other
parts of the country from May 12 to 25, which led to the
resignation of president Soeharto. 
</P>
