<HEADLINE> Two Mig-21s Crash over City, 11 injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Two Czech Mig-21 fighter jets
collided Monday over the city of Ceske Budejovice causing injury
and heavy damage.
</P>
<P>
The Czech News Agency said the collision occurred after the two
jets went out of control in a training exercise. One plane crashed
into an apartment block, destroying 18 apartments, injuring 11
people and setting 20 cars ablaze.
</P>
<P>
The second plane fell into a nearby field. Three airmen aboard
ejected successfully.
</P>
<P>
Following the accident, Czech Defense Minister Michal Lobkowicz
rushed to the scene.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the collision is under investigation. Over the
past three years, eight military jets have crashed in the Czech
Republic, and parliamentary members have strongly urged
disciplinary action against those held to be accountable. 
</P>
