<HEADLINE> Panama's Banana Exports to Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Panama banana exports will drop
by 10 million boxes (each weighing 18.14 kilograms) due to strike,
drought and restrictions on the quota imposed by the European
Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Rodolfo Espino, director of the National Banana Commission,
said that the multi-national banana company Puerto Armuelle was
the worst affected with a loss of 60 million U.S. dollars
predicted this year.
</P>
<P>
The company planned to export 34 million boxes of bananas this
year, but lowered its forecast to 24 million boxes after workers
in the sector held a 57-day strike, resulting in the lay-offs of
257 workers.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the company earned 266 million dollars from the sale
of the fruit, the country's main export. 
</P>
