<HEADLINE> Camacho Becomes Real Madrid Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Jose Antonio Camacho was finally
signed as the Real Madrid coach late on Monday night, according to
Spanish radio stations.
</P>
<P>
Camacho played 16 seasons with Real during the 1970s
and 1980s and notched up 81 Spanish caps.
</P>
<P>
Camacho made his first entry into the world of coaching at Real
Madrid when he worked as an assistant to the legendary Alfredo
di Stefano briefly during the 1989-90 season.
</P>
<P>
After taking control of the another Madrid side Rayo
Vallecano, Camacho coached Espanyol for three seasons. 
</P>
