<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Approves Sea Use Ruling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The government of China's Shandong
Province recently approved a rule on the use of marine areas that
requires local maritime departments to arrange the use of the sea
in line with national economic development, social progress, and
natural conditions in marine areas.
</P>
<P>
They are asked to clearly define which sea areas can be
developed, which are to be protected, which are for special
utilization, and which to be reserved.
</P>
<P>
It also has provisions on limits of government authority in use
of marine areas and prohibits the random transfer, rent,
mortgaging, or occupation of sea areas without permission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
