<HEADLINE> Russian Communist Leader Arrives to Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, June 8, (Xinhua) -- Russian Communist party leader
Gennady Zyuganov arrived here Monday for a four day visit to Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Zyuganov is the first Russian Communist leader to come to the
island country after the disintegration of the Soviet Union in
1991.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival, Zyuganov expressed his desire to discuss
issues of common interest with the Cuban Communist Party (PCC) and
update his knowledge of the current situation in the island.
</P>
<P>
He is scheduled to meet with the member of the PCC political
bureau and chief of international affairs, Jose Ramon Balaguer,
chancellor Roberto Robaina and parliament National Assembly
Ricardo Alarcon.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, Zyuganov will end his visit to Cuba, the last leg
of his Latin America trip, which has already taken him to Brazil
and Argentina. 
</P>
