<HEADLINE> Ancient Tombs Found in South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A large group of ancient tombs
dating back to the Eastern Han Dynasty (25-220) have been found in
Panyu, a city in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Chinese archeologists have unearthed five tombs in an area of
30,000 square meters at a village in Zhongcun Township.
</P>
<P>
Some 51 pieces of bronze and pottery articles as well as agate
objects have been discovered in the tombs. At the same time,
archeologists have unearthed 21 pottery, stone and iron relics
from two wells near the tombs dating back to the Ming Dynasty
(1368-1644). 
</P>
</TEXT>
