<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councillor Meets UN President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councillor Luo
Gan talked with U.N. General Assembly President on relations
between China and United Nations during their meeting here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Luo is attending, as head of the Chinese delegation, the
anti-drug special session of the U.S. General Assembly at the U.N.
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Hennadly Y. Udovenko, the U.N. President and former Foreign
Minister of Ukraine, told the Chinese leader that China is playing
an important role in the United Nations. No matter acting as the
U.N. President or a Ukraine government official, he said, he
always kept a clear mind that Taiwan is a part of China which can
never be severed.
</P>
<P>
While expressing his appreciation for the excellent work of
Udovenko during his term of presidency, Luo Gan also thanked the
U.N. president for the firm stand of the United Nations in
thwarting the attempt of Taiwan to "return" to the U.N.
</P>
<P>
Luo spoke highly of the traditional good relationship between
China and Ukraine, saying that it will help develop bilateral
relations if the two countries continue their mutual support in
the international affairs. Udovenko said that Ukraine pays great
attention to developing relations with China. It admires the great
achievement China has made in developing economy, he said, adding
that Ukraine would learn the Chinese experience.  
