<HEADLINE> S. Africa Mourns Nigerian Leader's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The South African government
Monday night mourned the death of Nigerian leader Sani Abacha.
</P>
<P>
"The South African government expresses its condolences to the
family of General Sani Abacha and to the Nigerian nation at his
sudden and untimely death," the Foreign Affairs Department said
in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Pretoria paid tribute to the "positive contribution" which
Abacha recently made toward the return of democracy in Sierra
Leone as leader of the Economic Community of West African states
and the west African peacekeeping force ECOMOG.
</P>
<P>
"It is our hope that the good relations that exist between our
two countries will persist, and that the path to democracy in
Nigeria will be pursued to its full conclusion," the statement
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
