<HEADLINE> Portugal Stresses Political Will in Anti-Drug Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 8 (Xinhua) -- There can be no efficient
fight against drugs without a determined political will, said
Portuguese President Branco de Sampaio here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the U.N. special session on drugs which opened here
today, the President said financial resources are fundamental to
help countries that are committed to the eradication and
replacement of illicit crops.
</P>
<P>
Portugal recently increased its contribution to the United
Nations Drug Control Program (UNDCP) and will "give a financial
expression of its political will to cooperate with the U.N. in
that field", he said.
</P>
<P>
The President noted that the international community's joint
response to the world drug problem must reflect a solidarity on
the assumption of a shared responsibility. 
</P>
</TEXT>
