<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile Urges Substantive Steps in Fighting Illicit Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Addressing the Special Session of the General Assembly of the
United Nations on World drug Problem, President Frei Ruiz-Tagle
said the Special Session is taking up one of the problem in most
urgent need of solution in today's world.
</P>
<P>
The president said the drug problem has become a widely
sensitive factor in the relations among states, and has earned
priority attention of multilateral and regional bodies and the
allocation of a considerable volume of resources to prevent and
limit the growth of demand and to control and halt illicit
trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The President said it is essential and urgent to tackle the
problem jointly, and this is being reiterated again today. But the
international community has not been capable of applying this
reasoning.
</P>
<P>
Frei Ruiz-Tagle said in the context of today's world and in
order to be really effective in bringing about a decrease in
consumption and the eradication of supply, the international
community has to act on the basis of mutual confidence,
solidarity and reciprocal and horizontal assistance, with full
respect for domestic law and the principles of international law.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
