<HEADLINE> Ugandan Official Calls for Fight Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan Minister of Internal
Affairs Tom Butime called on the general public to offer
information about terrorists in the country.
</P>
<P>
In a statement available here Monday, the Minister said that
the remnants of the Allied Democratic Rebels have infiltrated
into towns from countryside to commit acts of terrorism against
the common people.
</P>
<P>
He said the ultimate purpose of the rebels is to overthrow the
government by resorting to armed struggle and terrorism. The
recent bomb and grenade blasts in Kampala and other areas are
part of their terrorism plan.
</P>
<P>
According to him, some arrests were made in kampala in
connection with the blasts.
</P>
<P>
Butime revealed that a total of 38 criminals appeared in the
Kasese Magistrates Court Monday on charges of treason.
</P>
<P>
He said his ministry is commited to the principles of the rule
of law and that any people who commit offences will be dealt with
irrespective of their status.
</P>
<P>
Security personnel in the country have intensified their
activities aimed at bringing all the perpetrators of such
terrorist activities to book so that the greater interests of the
rights of the people prevail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
